				<div class="comment-meta post-meta" role="complementary">
					<h2 class="comment-author">
													<a class="comment-author-link" href="http://nakedsecurity.sophos.com" itemprop="author">Mark Stockley</a>
											</h2>
					<time class="comment-meta-item" datetime="2016-03-31T11:21-04:00" itemprop="datePublished"><a href="#comment-7452" itemprop="url">31 March 2016 at 11:21 am</a></time>
														</div>
				<div class="comment-content post-content" itemprop="text">
					<p>It&#8217;s an in-depth technical article so the information is in there, but easily missed.</p>
<p>The article explains in the third paragraph that the malware is distributed using the Angler exploit kit, via the CVE-2015-0311 Flash vulnerability. The vulnerability &#8220;allows remote attackers to execute arbitrary code&#8221;, which means that the malware doesn&#8217;t need to ask for your confirmation to run.</p>
					<a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='https://news.sophos.com/en-us/2016/01/06/the-current-state-of-ransomware-teslacrypt/?replytocom=7452#respond' data-commentid="7452" data-postid="30498" data-belowelement="comment-7452" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Mark Stockley" aria-label='Reply to Mark Stockley'>Reply</a>				</div>
			</div>

